  "texts": [
    "To assess the performance of these methods, we define three distinct scenarios: 1) Fine-tuning an SFT model, 2) Fine-tuning a pre-trained model, and 3) Finetuning an instruction model.",
    "In scenario 1, we employ a supervised fine-tuned model on chat completion and fine-tune it with different alignment methods.",
    "In scenario 2, we omit the SFT phase and directly fine-tune a pre-trained model with alignment methods.",
    "In scenario 3, we skip the SFT phase and utilize an instruction-tuned model as the base model, fine-tuning it with alignment methods.",
    "The results indicate that in the standard alignment process, KTO outperforms other methods across all tasks except for multi-task understanding."
  ],
